body_html:
Ok, I found the Problem:

file: tensorflow/compiler/aot/tfcompile.bzl:277

def target_llvm_triple():
  """Returns the target LLVM triple to be used for compiling the target."""
  # TODO(toddw): Add target_triple for other targets.  For details see:
  # http://llvm.org/docs/doxygen/html/Triple_8h_source.html
  return select({
      "//tensorflow:android_arm": "armv7-none-android",
      "//tensorflow:android_arm64": "aarch64-none-android",
      "//tensorflow:android_x86": "i686-none-android",
      "//tensorflow:linux_ppc64le": "ppc64le-ibm-linux-gnu",
      "//conditions:default": "x86_64-pc-linux",
  })

Adding

"//tensorflow:darwin": "x86_64-none-darwin",

fixes the problem. I can provide a pull request for that, but it seems there are more targets missing.
Maybe someone with more overview of supported platforms (@tatatodd ?) can take a look here.

body:
Ok, I found the Problem:

file: tensorflow/compiler/aot/tfcompile.bzl:277
```
def target_llvm_triple():
  """Returns the target LLVM triple to be used for compiling the target."""
  # TODO(toddw): Add target_triple for other targets.  For details see:
  # http://llvm.org/docs/doxygen/html/Triple_8h_source.html
  return select({
      "//tensorflow:android_arm": "armv7-none-android",
      "//tensorflow:android_arm64": "aarch64-none-android",
      "//tensorflow:android_x86": "i686-none-android",
      "//tensorflow:linux_ppc64le": "ppc64le-ibm-linux-gnu",
      "//conditions:default": "x86_64-pc-linux",
  })
```

Adding 
```
"//tensorflow:darwin": "x86_64-none-darwin",
```
fixes the problem. I can provide a pull request for that, but it seems there are more targets missing.
Maybe someone with more overview of supported platforms (@tatatodd ?) can take a look here.
